#. <section class="sutta" id="an8.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "an8.1:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8"
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Mettāvagga"
msgstr "1. Love"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 1. Mettāsutta → mettānisaṃsasuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Mettāsutta"
msgstr "1. The Benefits of Love"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.150"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "an8.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "an8.1:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "an8.1:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "an8.1:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "an8.1:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "an8.1:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "an8.1:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Mettāya, bhikkhave, cetovimuttiyā āsevitāya bhāvitāya bahulīkatāya "
"yānīkatāya vatthukatāya anuṭṭhitāya paricitāya susamāraddhāya aṭṭhānisaṃsā "
"pāṭikaṅkhā."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, you can expect eight benefits when the heart’s release by love "
"has been cultivated, developed, and practiced, made a vehicle and a basis, "
"kept up, consolidated, and properly implemented."

msgctxt "an8.1:2.2"
msgid "Katame aṭṭha?"
msgstr "What eight?"

msgctxt "an8.1:2.3"
msgid ""
"Sukhaṃ supati, sukhaṃ paṭibujjhati, na pāpakaṃ supinaṃ passati, manussānaṃ "
"piyo hoti, amanussānaṃ piyo hoti, devatā rakkhanti, nāssa aggi vā visaṃ vā "
"satthaṃ vā kamati, uttariṃ appaṭivijjhanto brahmalokūpago hoti."
msgstr ""
"You sleep well. You wake happily. You don’t see bad dreams. Humans love you. "
"Non-humans love you. Deities protect you. You can’t be harmed by fire, "
"poison, or blade. If you don’t reach any higher, you’ll be reborn in a "
"Brahmā realm."

msgctxt "an8.1:2.4"
msgid ""
"Mettāya, bhikkhave, cetovimuttiyā āsevitāya bhāvitāya bahulīkatāya "
"yānīkatāya vatthukatāya anuṭṭhitāya paricitāya susamāraddhāya ime "
"aṭṭhānisaṃsā pāṭikaṅkhāti."
msgstr ""
"You can expect these eight benefits when the heart’s release by love has "
"been cultivated, developed, and practiced, made a vehicle and a basis, kept "
"up, consolidated, and properly implemented."

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "an8.1:3.1"
msgid "Yo ca mettaṃ bhāvayati,"
msgstr "A mindful one who develops"

#. <br>
#. VAR: paṭissato → patissato (bj)
msgctxt "an8.1:3.2"
msgid "appamāṇaṃ paṭissato;"
msgstr "limitless love"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.1:3.3"
msgid "Tanū saṃyojanā honti,"
msgstr "weakens the fetters,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.1:3.4"
msgid "passato upadhikkhayaṃ."
msgstr "seeing the ending of attachments."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.151"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "an8.1:4.1"
msgid "Ekampi ce pāṇamaduṭṭhacitto,"
msgstr "Loving just one creature with a hateless heart"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.1:4.2"
msgid "Mettāyati kusalī tena hoti;"
msgstr "makes you a good person."

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.1:4.3"
msgid "Sabbe ca pāṇe manasānukampī,"
msgstr "Compassionate for all creatures,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.1:4.4"
msgid "Pahūtamariyo pakaroti puññaṃ."
msgstr "a noble one creates abundant merit."

# i don’t think “sage” fits isi well here. It seems to me the earliest meaning of the term is something like “man of power, chosen one”, which I draw on here. By the time of the suttas it already comes to connotate a legendary figure.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "an8.1:5.1"
msgid "Ye sattasaṇḍaṃ pathaviṃ vijetvā,"
msgstr "The royal potentates conquered this land"

# BB has “performing sacrifices”. But yajamana refers to those, usually khattiyas as here, who sponsor the sacrifice, not the brahmins performing it. See Olivelle, Early Upanishads, p. 16.
#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.1:5.2"
msgid "Rājisayo yajamānā anupariyagā;"
msgstr "and traveled around sponsoring sacrifices—"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.1:5.3"
msgid "Assamedhaṃ purisamedhaṃ,"
msgstr "horse sacrifice, human sacrifice,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.1:5.4"
msgid "Sammāpāsaṃ vājapeyyaṃ niraggaḷaṃ."
msgstr ""
"the sacrifices of the ‘stick-casting’, the ‘royal soma drinking’, and the "
"‘unbarred’."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "an8.1:6.1"
msgid "Mettassa cittassa subhāvitassa,"
msgstr "These are not worth a sixteenth part"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.1:6.2"
msgid "Kalampi te nānubhavanti soḷasiṃ;"
msgstr "of the mind developed with love,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.1:6.3"
msgid "Candappabhā tāragaṇāva sabbe,"
msgstr "as all the constellations of stars"

#. <br>
#. VAR: soḷasiṃ → ayaṃ pādo s1-3, pts1 potthakesu
msgctxt "an8.1:6.4"
msgid "Yathā na agghanti kalampi soḷasiṃ."
msgstr "aren’t worth a sixteenth part of the moon’s light."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
msgctxt "an8.1:7.1"
msgid "Yo na hanti na ghāteti,"
msgstr "If you don’t kill or encourage others to kill,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.1:7.2"
msgid "na jināti na jāpaye;"
msgstr "don’t conquer or encourage others to conquer,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.1:7.3"
msgid "Mettaṃso sabbabhūtānaṃ,"
msgstr "with love for all sentient beings,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "an8.1:7.4"
msgid "veraṃ tassa na kenacī”ti."
msgstr "you’ll have no enmity for anyone.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.1:7.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr ""
